page.title: 09Parham Wood.
page.content: {Parham Wood}is an area of broad leaved woodland with a variety of trees and wildlife.There are oak,ash,wych elm, elder,hazel,holly,ivy,beech,walnut, goat willow,Scots pine,and birch trees in the the wood.There are also bushes like hawthorn and elm.There is a plantation of conifers near.There are many badgers in{Parham Wood}because it is a sandy area so it is simple to dig setts.There is also much other wildlife like rabbits,roe deer,pigeon, pheasants,rook,moles,weasels,stoats, voles,squirrels and foxes.Moss and bracken grow under trees.Also there are some flowers like ragged robin, bluebells and buttercups.
